While the spherical distance, $z_{12}$, is always less than unity, the hyperbolic one, $Z_{12}$, can acquire any value because of the Minkowskian signature of the metric.

All geodesics on the hyperboloid of Fig. (\ref{fig20}) are curves that are cut out on it by planes going through the origin of the ambient Minkowski space--time. (The situation here is absolutely similar to the case of the sphere, as can be understood after the Wick rotation.) Hence, space-like geodesics are ellipses, time-like ones are hyperbolas and light-like are straight generatrix lines of the hyperboloid, which are also light--like in the ambient Minkowski space--time.

